<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="111" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1615,2038]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,1687,1713]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[329,524,1687,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[329,524,1687,1713]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">Paragus thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[532,597,1687,1713]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[532,597,1687,1713]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is by habitus most similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stcnescu" authorityName="Stcnescu" box="[934,1174,1687,1713]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[934,1064,1687,1713]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
Stćnescu
</taxonomicName>
, but easily distinguishable by the following characters: mesonotum of 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[697,817,1723,1749]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[697,817,1723,1749]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[824,888,1723,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[824,888,1723,1749]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
covered with longer erect whitish-yellow pile in contrast to short yellow adpressed pile in 
<taxonomicName box="[614,742,1759,1785]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[614,742,1759,1785]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; microtrichose maculae at the end of transverse suture present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[180,300,1795,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[180,300,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[307,371,1795,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[307,371,1795,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but lack in 
<taxonomicName box="[510,639,1795,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[510,639,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; punctuation of mesonotum scarce in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[1068,1188,1795,1821]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1068,1188,1795,1821]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1195,1259,1795,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1195,1259,1795,1821]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but dense in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; femora dark-brown/black basally in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[669,787,1831,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[669,787,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[792,855,1831,1857]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[792,855,1831,1857]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, while orange-yellow in 
<taxonomicName box="[1130,1257,1831,1857]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[1130,1257,1831,1857]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; tergum 1 black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[179,297,1867,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[179,297,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[302,365,1867,1893]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[302,365,1867,1893]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, and medially reddish in 
<taxonomicName box="[642,764,1867,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[642,764,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P.oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; microtrichose fasciae on terga 2–4 distinct in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[1279,1397,1867,1893]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[1279,1397,1867,1893]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but absent or scarce in 
<taxonomicName box="[444,572,1903,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[444,572,1903,1929]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; microtrichia on terga completely whitish-yellow, while in 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1364,1903,1929]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">
<emphasis box="[1236,1364,1903,1929]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. oltenicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
partly black; black transversal maculae on terga 2–4 lack in 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[763,883,1939,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[763,883,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[891,956,1939,1965]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[891,956,1939,1965]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but usually present in 
<emphasis box="[1223,1360,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicName box="[1223,1356,1939,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oltenicus">P. oltenicus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Based on the male genitalia 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[391,510,1975,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Paragus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thracusi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[391,510,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">P. thracusi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[516,579,1975,2001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[516,579,1975,2001]" pageId="8" pageNumber="111" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is immediately recognizable by the characters of hypandrium: pointed, hood shaped paramere and cliff shaped lingula.
</paragraph>
