<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="9" pageNumber="112" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1583,2042]" lastBlockId="10.[151,1437,151,753]" lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="113" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,516,1583,1610]" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">
Description. MALE. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[454,516,1583,1610]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Head</emphasis>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[534,607,1584,1610]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1477,1501]" captionTargetBox="[167,1426,191,1440]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1454]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A head, lateral view, B head, frontal view, C abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402974/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Figs 7</figureCitation>
A–B). Face cream-yellow, with a faint brown macula on facial tubercle; ventral margin of face dark-brown/black, except the light-yellow frontal part; face and frons covered with only whitish pile; antennae long, basoflagellomere elongated and pointed, about 1.5 times as long as scape and pedicel together; arista 0.7 times the length of basoflagellomere; antennae predominantly brown, except orange basal 2/3 of basoflagellomere ventrally and pedicel ventrally; arista light-brown basally and dark-brown apically; eye contiguity 0.75 times the length of ocellar triangle; eyes with two clearly visible vittae of white pile, typical of the nominal subgenus; vertical triangle covered with grayish microtrichia in front of frontal ocellus, covered with light-yellow pile; occiput whitish microtrichose and with light-yellow pile, and with silver pile in lower parts, turning yellowish in upper parts. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[359,451,1871,1898]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="112">Thorax.</emphasis>
Scutum black with paler anterior and posterior end of postalar callus, shiny, except two longitudinal submedian whitish microtrichose vittae ending at the level of transverse suture, and with two whitish microtrichose maculae at the end of transverse suture; mesonotum with scarce punctuation, and covered with longer erect whitish-yellow pile; metathoracic pleuron whitish microtrichose and pilose, except for the anteroventral part of posterior anepisternum and anepimeron, which are shining black; scutellum black in anterior half, orange-yellow in posterior half, without conspicuous teeth on posterior margin; wings hyaline, covered with microtrichia, except for basal cells, which are nearly entirely bare; halters light-brown, with a yellow knob; legs two colored, covered with whitish-yellow pile; femora dark-brown, black at base (pro- and mesofemora in basal 1/3, and metafemur in basal 2/3, except for tiny area near to the base yellow), and light-yellow apically; tibiae light-yellow in basal half, and dark-yellow in apical half, metatibia with brown submedian ring; tarsi orange-yellow (borders between tarsomeres black), basotarsomere of metatarsus little darker dorsally; claws yellow in basal half and black in the apical half. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[212,322,366,393]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Abdomen</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[341,432,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURE 7" captionStartId="9.[151,250,1477,1501]" captionTargetBox="[167,1426,191,1440]" captionTargetId="figure-19@9.[151,1436,181,1454]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURE 7. Male of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A head, lateral view, B head, frontal view, C abdomen, dorsal view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402974" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402974/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 7C</figureCitation>
). Abdomen predominantly red-brown, covered with whitish-yellow pile and with three pairs of whitish-yellow microtrichose fasciae on terga 2–4; tergum 1 brown-black, more or less fused with tergum 2 that is dark-brown anteriorly to the microtrichose fasciae and laterally, while red-brown posteriorly; terga 3 and 4 predominantly red-brown, except dark-brown longitudinal areas near the lateral margins and on medial parts; tergum 5 red-brown; sterna translucent orange-brown (sternum 1 darker), covered with erect whitish pile; pregenital segment white microtrichose and pilose. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[615,783,546,573]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[799,869,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium in lateral view wide (
<figureCitation box="[1282,1371,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
) with clearly developed lingula cliff shaped (
<figureCitation box="[599,691,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
: l); lateral lobe of aedeagus (= inferior claspers) well developed, almost quadrilateral in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[559,648,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
: la); paramere (= superior claspers) pointed, hood shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1310,1374,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
A–B: p); ejaculatory apodeme pendulum like (
<figureCitation box="[615,706,655,681]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8C</figureCitation>
); epandrium in lateral view narrow, with narrow, not prominent cercus (
<figureCitation box="[239,327,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
); surstylus (= styles) a little shorter than theca of epandrium (
<figureCitation box="[1027,1116,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8E</figureCitation>
: sst), curved and tapering in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[296,387,727,753]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1924,1948]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,784,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-304@10.[151,1436,777,1900]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 8. Male genitalia of Paragus thracusi sp. n. A hypandrium, lateral view, B hypandrium, ventral view, C ejaculatory apodeme, lateral view, D epandrium, dorsal view, E epandrium, lateral view. aa—aedeagal apodeme, ae—aedeagus, ce—cercus, l—lingula, la—lateral lobe of aedeagus, m—minis, p—postgonit, sst—surstylus. Scale bar 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402976" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402976/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="113">Fig. 8D</figureCitation>
: sst).
</paragraph>
